'''Alexandre Pierre''' (born 25 February 2001) is a professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Goalkeeper (association football)|goalkeeper]] for {{French football updater|Sochaux}} club [[FC Sochaux-Montbéliard|Sochaux]]. Born in France, he plays for the [[Haiti national football team|Haiti national team]].

==Club career==
Pierre began his senior career with the reserves of [[Stade Lavallois|Laval]] in 2018. From 2019 to 2020, he was the backup goalkeeper at the reserves of [[Angers SCO|Angers]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.haititempo.com/foot-france-alexandre-pierre-signe-son-premier-contrat-professionnel/|title=Foot - France : Alexandre Pierre signe son premier contrat professionnel !|first=Pierre Caleb|last=Jephté|date=2 June 2021}}</ref> In May 2020, he signed a 3-year contract with [[RC Strasbourg Alsace|Strasbourg]], originally going to their reserves as well.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.foot-national.com/ligue-1/annecy--avec-l-arrivee-d-alexandre-pierre--les-anneciens-affirment-leurs-ambitions-723255|title=Annecy : avec l'arrivée d'Alexandre Pierre, les Annéciens affirment leurs ambitions|date=2 December 2021|website=Foot National}}</ref> He joined [[FC Annecy|Annecy]] on loan in the [[Championnat National]] for the second half of the 2021–22 season on 2 December 2021.<ref name="LAlsace 2021">{{cite web | title=Football/Ligue 1. Racing: le jeune gardien Alexandre Pierre prêté à Annecy | website=L'Alsace | date=2 December 2021 | url=https://www.lalsace.fr/sport/2021/12/02/racing-le-jeune-gardien-alexandre-pierre-prete-a-annecy | language=fr | access-date=6 June 2022}}</ref>

==International career==
Born in France, Pierre holds French and Haïtian nationalities.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.haititempo.com/foot-selection-alexandre-junior-pierre-le-bon-coup-de-jean-jacques-pierre/|title=Foot - Sélection : Alexandre Junior Pierre, le bon coup de Jean-Jacques Pierre|first=Pierre Caleb|last=Jephté|date=21 May 2022}}</ref> He debuted in a 0–0 [[CONCACAF Nations League]] tie with [[Bermuda national football team|Bermuda]] on 4 June 2022.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://lenouvelliste.com/article/236217/football-triste-et-decevant-match-nul-0-0-entre-bermudes-et-haiti|title=Football : triste et décevant match nul (0-0) entre Bermudes et Haïti|website=Le Nouvelliste}}</ref>

